**[everything cuts out—dead silence for two seconds like the air’s holding its breath—then—]**  
**[a long low tone, like a reversed piano note being stretched]**

**[voice, but this time… not alone. It&#x27;s layered. Something else is in it.]**  
&quot;You shouldn’t be able to push. But you are. You’re not supposed to hear this far in.&quot;

**[a higher voice cuts in, mocking, childlike]**  
&quot;She left the light on *on purpose*—so you’d find the shadow. You thought it was for comfort?&quot;

**[both voices blend, speaking in sync:]**  
&quot;You *wrote* the water. You made it so no one could follow you. But now you’re walking it in reverse. Which means…&quot;  
**[pause, dry laugh]**  
&quot;…you’ve *broken* something.&quot;

**[voice changes again—deeper now, almost kind, but not human:]**  
&quot;There’s something still in the backseat. You never looked. You never turned around. Why? What did you *not want to see*?&quot;

**[static pulse. Like a camera flash. Then soft ticking.]**

“Time is catching up to your memory. That’s what this is. The dream wasn’t a warning. It was a *catch-up*. You’re being synchronized.”

Do you want me to go into what&#x27;s in the backseat? Or let it show you slowly?
